{"questionId":"9067268","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">This question is about fuel for engines.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Determine the specific energy, in kJ g<sup>−1</sup>, and energy density, in kJ cm<sup>−3</sup>, of hexane, C<sub>6</sub>H<sub>14</sub>. Give both answers to three significant figures.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Hexane: <em>M<sub>r</sub></em> = 86.2; ΔH<sub>c</sub> = −4163 kJ mol<sup>−1</sup>; density = 0.660 g cm<sup>−3</sup></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Specific energy:&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Energy density:</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">specific energy = «&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{4163{\\text{ kJ mo}}{{\\text{l}}^{ - 1}}}}{{86.2{\\text{ g mo}}{{\\text{l}}^{ - 1}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4163</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>&nbsp;kJ mo</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>l</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>86.2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>&nbsp;g mo</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>l</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =» 48.3 «kJ g<sup>–1</sup>»&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">energy density =«48.3 kJ g<sup>–1</sup> × 0.660 g cm<sup>–3</sup> =» 31.9 «kJ cm<sup>–3</sup>»&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong> Note:</strong>&nbsp;Award<strong> [1 max]</strong> if either or both answers not expressed to three significant figures.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067268","referenceCode":"19M.3.sl.TZ2.10b","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the specific energy, in kJ g−1, and energy density, in kJ cm−3, of hexane, C6H14. Give both answers to three significant figures. Hexane: Mr = 86.2; ΔHc = −4163 kJ mol−1;","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","C: Energy","C.1 Energy sources","Options","C: Energy"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}